================================================================================
MICROSOFT.AGENTS.AI AND MICROSOFT.EXTENSIONS.AI API SURFACE SUMMARY
================================================================================

PROJECT: ResearchAgent (uses Microsoft.Agents.AI 1.6.2 and Microsoft.Extensions.AI 10.5.1+)
PACKAGES ANALYZED:
  - microsoft.agents.ai@1.6.2
  - microsoft.extensions.ai@10.5.1
  - microsoft.extensions.ai.abstractions@10.6.0

================================================================================
1. CREATING AN AGENT
================================================================================

MAIN AGENT CLASS: ChatClientAgent (Microsoft.Agents.AI)
  - Delegates to an IChatClient implementation for LLM calls
  - Provides the main AI agent orchestration capabilities
  - Supports sessions, tool invocation, and streaming responses

CONSTRUCTOR SIGNATURES:

  ChatClientAgent(
    IChatClient chatClient,
    string instructions = null,
    string name = null,
    string description = null,
    IList<AITool> tools = null,
    ILoggerFactory loggerFactory = null,
    IServiceProvider services = null
  )

  ChatClientAgent(
    IChatClient chatClient,
    ChatClientAgentOptions options,
    ILoggerFactory loggerFactory = null,
    IServiceProvider services = null
  )

BUILDER EXTENSIONS (Microsoft.Extensions.AI):

  // Create from a ChatClientBuilder pipeline
  AIAgent BuildAIAgent(
    ChatClientBuilder builder,
    ChatClientAgentOptions options,
    ILoggerFactory loggerFactory = null,
    IServiceProvider services = null
  )

  // Create directly from IChatClient
  ChatClientAgent AsAIAgent(
    IChatClient chatClient,
    ChatClientAgentOptions options,
    ILoggerFactory loggerFactory = null,
    IServiceProvider services = null
  )

================================================================================
2. KEY CONFIGURATION CLASSES
================================================================================

A. ChatClientAgentOptions (Microsoft.Agents.AI)
   Encapsulates all configuration for a ChatClientAgent:

   Properties:
   - Id: string (agent identifier)
   - Name: string (display name)
   - Description: string (agent purpose/capabilities)
   - ChatOptions: ChatOptions (default chat settings)
   - ChatHistoryProvider: ChatHistoryProvider (optional history persistence)
   - AIContextProviders: List<AIContextProvider> (additional context sources)
   - UseProvidedChatClientAsIs: bool (skip default decorators)
   - ClearOnChatHistoryProviderConflict: bool
   - WarnOnChatHistoryProviderConflict: bool
   - ThrowOnChatHistoryProviderConflict: bool
   - RequirePerServiceCallChatHistoryPersistence: bool
   - EnableMessageInjection: bool

B. ChatOptions (Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions)
   Core chat request configuration:

   Key Properties:
   - ConversationId: string (associate with existing conversation)
   - Instructions: string (per-request system instructions)
   - Temperature: double? (0.0-2.0, controls randomness)
   - MaxOutputTokens: int? (max response length)
   - TopP: double? (nucleus sampling)
   - TopK: int? (most probable tokens to consider)
   - FrequencyPenalty: float? (reduce repeated tokens)
   - PresencePenalty: float? (affect token probability based on existence)
   - Seed: int? (reproducibility control)
   - ModelId: string (specific model to use)
   - StopSequences: IList<string> (sequences to stop generation)
   - AllowMultipleToolCalls: bool (allow multiple tools in one response)
   - ToolMode: ToolMode? (None, Auto, Required)
   - Tools: IList<AITool> (available functions)
   - AllowBackgroundResponses: bool (streaming continuation support)
   - ContinuationToken: ResponseContinuationToken (for resumable responses)
   - AdditionalProperties: IDictionary<string, object>

C. ChatClientAgentRunOptions (Microsoft.Agents.AI)
   Runtime options for specific agent invocations:

   Properties:
   - ChatOptions: ChatOptions (options for this specific run)
   - ChatClientFactory: Func<IChatClient, IChatClient>? (decorate chat client)

   Inherits from AgentRunOptions:
   - MaximumIterations: int (max agentic loops)
   - ThrowExceptionOnAgentFailure: bool
   - ThrowExceptionOnToolFailure: bool

================================================================================
3. HOW TOOLS/FUNCTIONS ARE REGISTERED
================================================================================

TOOL REPRESENTATION: AITool (Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions)

  public class AITool
  {
      public string Name { get; }  // Function name
      public AIFunctionDeclaration Function { get; }  // Metadata
      public AIFunction? Implementation { get; }  // Optional invokable implementation
      public IDictionary<string, object>? AdditionalProperties { get; }
  }

FUNCTION DECLARATION: AIFunctionDeclaration

  Represents function metadata:
  - JsonSchema: JsonNode describing function and parameters (OpenAI format)
  - ReturnJsonSchema: JsonNode for return type

TOOL REGISTRATION PATTERNS:

1. Via ChatOptions.Tools (for any invocation):
   var options = new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(
     new ChatOptions
     {
       Tools = new List<AITool>
       {
         new AITool 
         { 
           Name = "get_weather",
           Function = new AIFunctionDeclaration { JsonSchema = ... }
         }
       }
     }
   );

2. Via ChatClientAgentOptions (default for agent):
   var agentOptions = new ChatClientAgentOptions
   {
     ChatOptions = new ChatOptions
     {
       Tools = new List<AITool> { ... }
     }
   };
   var agent = new ChatClientAgent(chatClient, agentOptions);

3. Via ChatClientAgent constructor:
   var agent = new ChatClientAgent(
     chatClient,
     instructions: "...",
     tools: new List<AITool> { ... }
   );

4. FunctionInvokingChatClient Decorator (Microsoft.Extensions.AI):
   // Auto-invoke functions declared as AIFunction
   var chatClient = new ChatClientBuilder(innerClient)
     .UseFunctionInvoking()
     .Build();

   // Then provide AITool items with AIFunction implementations
   var options = new ChatOptions
   {
     Tools = AIFunctionFactory.Create(
       new Func<string, Task<string>>(GetWeatherAsync),
       new AIFunctionFactoryOptions { ... }
     )
   };

================================================================================
4. HOW TO INVOKE THE AGENT AND GET RESPONSES
================================================================================

AGENT SESSION: ChatClientAgentSession
  Represents a conversation state/thread:
  - ConversationId: string? (optional service-managed ID)
  - Messages: IList<ChatMessage> (conversation history)

CREATE SESSION:
  var session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync(cancellationToken);
  // OR to resume:
  var session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync(conversationId, cancellationToken);

AGENT RESPONSE PATTERNS:

A. Run with Text Message:
   AgentResponse response = await agent.RunAsync(
     message: "What is the weather?",
     session: session,
     options: new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(),
     cancellationToken: CancellationToken.None
   );

   // Access response
   foreach (var msg in response.Messages)
   {
     if (msg.Role == ChatRole.Assistant)
     {
       var text = msg.Content[0]?.Text;
     }
   }

B. Run with ChatMessage(s):
   var messages = new List<ChatMessage>
   {
     new ChatMessage(ChatRole.User, "Get the weather in Seattle")
   };

   AgentResponse response = await agent.RunAsync(
     messages: messages,
     session: session,
     options: new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(),
     cancellationToken: CancellationToken.None
   );

C. Run with Structured Output (Generic Response<T>):
   var response = await agent.RunAsync<WeatherInfo>(
     message: "What's the weather?",
     serializerOptions: new JsonSerializerOptions(),
     session: session,
     options: new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(),
     cancellationToken: CancellationToken.None
   );

D. Streaming Response:
   await foreach (var update in agent.RunStreamingAsync(
     message: "What's the weather?",
     session: session,
     options: new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(),
     cancellationToken: CancellationToken.None
   ))
   {
     // Handle AgentResponseUpdate
   }

E. Run Without New Message (use session context):
   AgentResponse response = await agent.RunAsync(
     session: session,
     options: new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(),
     cancellationToken: CancellationToken.None
   );

AGENT RESPONSE STRUCTURE: AgentResponse
  - Messages: IList<ChatMessage> (all messages in conversation)
  - RawRepresentation: object? (LLM-specific response)

CHAT MESSAGE TYPES: ChatMessage (Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions)
  Properties:
  - Role: ChatRole (User, Assistant, System, Tool)
  - Content: IList<ChatContent> (text, images, function calls, etc.)
  - AuthorName: string? (who sent message)
  - RawRepresentation: object? (provider-specific data)

CHAT CONTENT TYPES:
  - TextContent: string Text
  - ImageContent: byte[] Data, string MediaType
  - FunctionCallContent: string Id, string FunctionName, string? Arguments (JSON)
  - FunctionResultContent: string FunctionId, object? Result

================================================================================
5. AGENTINVOKEOPTIONS / AGENT RUN OPTIONS
================================================================================

ChatClientAgentRunOptions (extends AgentRunOptions)

  Initialization:
  new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(ChatOptions chatOptions = null)
  new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(ChatClientAgentRunOptions copyCtor)

  Key Properties:

  ChatOptions ChatOptions
    - Provides chat client settings for this run
    - Merged with agent's default ChatOptions
    - Tools specified here are unioned with agent's default tools

  Func<IChatClient, IChatClient>? ChatClientFactory
    - Allows decorating/replacing chat client per-request
    - Useful for adding logging, caching, or other middleware
    - Example: (client) => new LoggingChatClient(client)

  Method:
  - Clone(): ChatClientAgentRunOptions

INHERITED FROM AGENT RUNOPT IONS:

  int MaximumIterations
    - Limits agentic loop iterations
    - Controls max tool-call/response cycles
    - Default: typically unlimited or very high
    - Use to prevent infinite loops

  bool ThrowExceptionOnAgentFailure
    - Whether to throw on agent-level errors

  bool ThrowExceptionOnToolFailure
    - Whether to throw when tools fail

================================================================================
6. TOOL CREATION AND FUNCTION FACTORY (Microsoft.Extensions.AI)
================================================================================

AIFunctionFactory (Microsoft.Extensions.AI)
  Static factory methods for creating AITool from methods:

  static IList<AITool> Create(
    Delegate method,
    AIFunctionFactoryOptions? options = null
  )

  static IList<AITool> Create(
    object? instance,
    string methodName,
    AIFunctionFactoryOptions? options = null
  )

  static IList<AITool> Create(
    Type type,
    AIFunctionFactoryOptions? options = null
  )

  Example:
  var tools = AIFunctionFactory.Create(
    new Func<string, Task<string>>(GetWeatherAsync),
    new AIFunctionFactoryOptions
    {
      FunctionName = "get_weather",
      Description = "Gets current weather"
    }
  );

AIFunctionFactoryOptions
  Properties:
  - FunctionName: string? (override method name)
  - Description: string? (function description)
  - ParameterDescriptions: IDictionary<string, string>? (param docs)
  - Parameters: IList<AIFunctionParameterMetadata>? (explicit param schema)

FUNCTION INVOCATION:

FunctionInvokingChatClient (Microsoft.Extensions.AI)
  - Decorator that auto-invokes AIFunction tools
  - Watches for FunctionCallContent in responses
  - Invokes matching functions and adds results back to conversation

  Configuration:
  var chatClient = new ChatClientBuilder(innerClient)
    .UseFunctionInvoking()  // Extension method
    .Build();

  // Then provide tools with implementations:
  var tools = AIFunctionFactory.Create(
    myWeatherFunction,
    new AIFunctionFactoryOptions { FunctionName = "get_weather" }
  );

  var response = await chatClient.GetResponseAsync(
    messages,
    new ChatOptions { Tools = tools }
  );

FunctionInvocationContext
  Information passed to function during invocation:
  - FunctionCallContent: The original function call
  - ChatClient: The client making the call
  - Messages: Full conversation history
  - Options: ChatOptions for the request
  - CancellationToken: For cancellation

================================================================================
7. KEY IChatClient INTERFACE (Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions)
================================================================================

public interface IChatClient : IAsyncDisposable
{
  Task<ChatResponse<ChatCompletionContent>> GetResponseAsync(
    IEnumerable<ChatMessage> chatMessages,
    ChatOptions? options = null,
    CancellationToken cancellationToken = default
  );

  IAsyncEnumerable<StreamingChatCompletionUpdate> GetStreamingResponseAsync(
    IEnumerable<ChatMessage> chatMessages,
    ChatOptions? options = null,
    CancellationToken cancellationToken = default
  );

  T? GetService<T>(object? key = null) where T : class;
}

RESPONSE TYPES:

  ChatResponse<T>
  - Results: IList<T>? (response content items)
  - Usage: CompletionTokensInfo? (token counts)
  - ModelId: string?
  - RawRepresentation: object?
  - AdditionalProperties: IDictionary<string, object>?

  StreamingChatCompletionUpdate
  - RoleUpdate, ContentUpdate, etc.
  - For streaming incremental responses

================================================================================
8. AGENT CONTEXT AND PROVIDERS (Microsoft.Agents.AI)
================================================================================

ChatHistoryProvider
  - Optional component to persist/retrieve chat history
  - Allows external chat storage (DB, service)
  - Called automatically by ChatClientAgent

AIContextProvider
  - Supplies additional context for each agent run
  - Examples: retrieve documents, external data
  - Results injected into system instructions or messages

Configure in ChatClientAgentOptions:
  var options = new ChatClientAgentOptions
  {
    ChatHistoryProvider = new MyCustomHistoryProvider(),
    AIContextProviders = new List<AIContextProvider>
    {
      new DocumentContextProvider(),
      new UserProfileProvider()
    }
  };

================================================================================
9. FULL WORKFLOW EXAMPLE
================================================================================

// 1. Create/get an IChatClient
var chatClient = new ChatClientBuilder(new OpenAIChatClient(...))
  .UseFunctionInvoking()  // Auto-invoke tools
  .Build();

// 2. Define tools
var tools = AIFunctionFactory.Create(
  new Func<string, Task<string>>(GetWeatherAsync),
  new AIFunctionFactoryOptions { FunctionName = "get_weather" }
);

// 3. Configure agent options
var agentOptions = new ChatClientAgentOptions
{
  Name = "WeatherAgent",
  Description = "Answers weather questions",
  Instructions = "You are a helpful weather assistant.",
  ChatOptions = new ChatOptions
  {
    Temperature = 0.7,
    Tools = tools,
    ToolMode = ToolMode.Auto
  }
};

// 4. Create agent
var agent = new ChatClientAgent(
  chatClient,
  agentOptions,
  loggerFactory: null,
  services: null
);

// 5. Create session
var session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync(CancellationToken.None);

// 6. Run agent
var response = await agent.RunAsync(
  message: "What's the weather in Seattle?",
  session: session,
  options: new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(),
  cancellationToken: CancellationToken.None
);

// 7. Process response
foreach (var msg in response.Messages)
{
  if (msg.Role == ChatRole.Assistant)
  {
    foreach (var content in msg.Content)
    {
      if (content is TextContent tc)
      {
        Console.WriteLine($"Assistant: {tc.Text}");
      }
    }
  }
}

